kingdom on the Arabian Sea

00:01:11.330 --> 00:01:13.430 align:middle line:90%
thousands of years ago?

00:01:13.430 --> 00:01:16.250 align:middle line:10%
Legendary tales
from the Mahabharata

00:01:16.250 --> 00:01:20.390 align:middle line:10%
recall the time when Krishna
left the Earth and his city,

00:01:20.390 --> 00:01:25.530 align:middle line:10%
referred to as Dvaraka,
was swallowed by the ocean.

00:01:25.530 --> 00:01:28.530 align:middle line:84%
Archeologists have
searched the entire coast

00:01:28.530 --> 00:01:31.770 align:middle line:84%
of Gujarat for clues
to approximate the date

00:01:31.770 --> 00:01:35.970 align:middle line:84%
of this once thriving area
known in mythology as Krishna's

00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:37.310 align:middle line:90%
Kingdom.

00:01:37.310 --> 00:01:39.980 align:middle line:84%
But will recent evidence
help us discover

00:01:39.980 --> 00:01:42.650 align:middle line:84%
the original
mythological gateway that

00:01:42.650 --> 00:01:47.390 align:middle line:84%
once stood as a shining and
sophisticated city 12,000 years

00:01:47.390 --> 00:01:49.895 align:middle line:90%
ago before the Great Flood?

00:01:49.895 --> 00:01:53.198 align:middle line:90%


00:01:53.198 --> 00:01:57.320 align:middle line:10%
>> In 2001, scientist from
the Indian government made

00:01:57.320 --> 00:02:00.770 align:middle line:10%
the discovery in the Gulf
of Khambhat that continues

00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:04.040 align:middle line:10%
to shake the foundations of
everything that archeologists

00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:07.640 align:middle line:10%
thought they believed and
was true about this part

00:02:07.640 --> 00:02:11.050 align:middle line:10%
of the world, about
Western India.

00:02:11.050 --> 00:02:13.270 align:middle line:84%
The scientists were
on a research vessel

00:02:13.270 --> 00:02:16.840 align:middle line:84%
and they were using sonar to
determine levels of pollution

00:02:16.840 --> 00:02:17.950 align:middle line:90%
in the water.

00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:21.640 align:middle line:84%
The sonar began to return
a signature that was

00:02:21.640 --> 00:02:23.530 align:middle line:90%
anything other than natural.

00:02:23.530 --> 00:02:27.130 align:middle line:84%
They were the outlines
of massive buildings,

00:02:27.130 --> 00:02:31.840 align:middle line:84%
a huge complex
stretching for miles.

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:35.050 align:middle line:84%
And this led to an
investigation that is still

00:02:35.050 --> 00:02:37.180 align:middle line:90%
controversial to this day.

00:02:37.180 --> 00:02:39.730 align:middle line:84%
The area is called
the Gulf of Khambhat.

00:02:39.730 --> 00:02:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And in Hindu traditions, there
has always been the belief

00:02:44.140 --> 00:02:46.090 align:middle line:84%
that there was a
city, some people

00:02:46.090 --> 00:02:48.580 align:middle line:84%
call them mythical
city of Dwarka,

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:51.280 align:middle line:84%
where Krishna and
the gods lived,

00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:55.060 align:middle line:84%
and this is where many of the
descriptions in the Mahabharata

00:02:55.060 --> 00:02:57.220 align:middle line:90%
are actually playing out.

00:02:57.220 --> 00:03:00.310 align:middle line:84%
Well, up until recently,
officially, these

00:03:00.310 --> 00:03:05.380 align:middle line:84%
were believed to be stories
to help convey a message

00:03:05.380 --> 00:03:08.650 align:middle line:84%
but not based on
anything that is factual.

00:03:08.650 --> 00:03:10.540 align:middle line:84%
The discovery in
the Gulf of Khambhat

00:03:10.540 --> 00:03:12.280 align:middle line:90%
has changed all of that.

00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:14.650 align:middle line:84%
